AGI - Pakistani security forces freed 190 passengers from the train seized by the Belucistan Liberation Front. The operation, which saw the elimination of 30 terrorists, is still in progress. The train traveled 450 passengers.&nbsp;
&nbsp;
The train traveled from Quetta to Peshawar. Some of the terrorists were wearing explosive vests. The Liberation Army of Belucistan (Bla) claimed to have eliminated 20 members of the security forces and initially took over 180 people hostage, threatening to execute them if security forces intervened.
&nbsp;
"The terrorists used women and children as shields. Security forces surrounded the terrorists and the exchange of gunshots," added a source.
The Bla targets self-determination of the region, and has already become the protagonist of attacks on Pakistani security forces and Chinese investments in the region.&nbsp;

